Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

This adds a new field to the Image domain object to keep trace of original image's state. I doubt if this is a correct location to do it.
What I would suggest is to use some common system to keep track of all the changes of the properties.
There is a patch which does it (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/123722/), however it does not save the original values of changed attributes, just their names.  I would suggest to rebase your patch based on that one and extend the functionality of StateTrackingObject to include the original values of modified properties.

Patch Set 18:

Ian, thank you very much! But I was going to abandon this patch for several reasons:

1. It was built on Alexander's commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/123722/ and the whole idea was wrong. We shouldn't use inheritance there, but create another domain layer. Mark Washenberger mentioned this in his comment.

2. The goal we wanted to reach was get rid of race conditions during data update. But it turns out that the solution doesn't work anyway, because there are many other places where races may occur. https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/liberty-glance-domain-model

2. This bug has already been fixed by Zhi Yan's commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/144464/. I don't like this idea to have 'from_state' parameter in v2, but anyway it works.
